In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 13-19, 2009, as National Employer Support of the Guard and Reserve Week. He acknowledges the important role that citizens serving in the Guard and Reserve play in protecting the country's freedom and security. The President honors the courageous members of the Guard and Reserve and their employers, who support them and strengthen the Armed Forces. He recognizes the sacrifices made by these individuals, both in their civilian and military lives, and expresses gratitude to the businesses and organizations that enable them to fulfill their military duties while maintaining their professional careers. The President calls on Americans, state and local officials, private organizations, and military commanders to observe this week with appropriate ceremonies and activities.